---
import SidebarLayout from '../../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';
import "../../../styles/global.css";
---

<SidebarLayout app="python">
  <h1 class="text-xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-5 text-custom-accent text-center">
    If Statements
  </h1>

  <section class="mb-5 space-y-6 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed text-custom-secondary">
    <p>
      Conditional statements allow your program to make decisions and execute different code blocks based on conditions. Python uses <code>if</code>, <code>elif</code>, and <code>else</code> statements for conditional logic.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">Basic If Statements</h2>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-lg p-3 sm:p-4 my-4">
      <pre class="text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap"><code>{`# Simple if statement
age = 18

if age >= 18:
    print("You are an adult")

# if-else statement
temperature = 25

if temperature > 30:
    print("It's hot outside")
else:
    print("It's not too hot")

# if-elif-else chain
score = 85

if score >= 90:
    grade = "A"
elif score >= 80:
    grade = "B"
elif score >= 70:
    grade = "C"
else:
    grade = "F"

print(f"Your grade is: {grade}")

# Nested if statements
age = 25
has_license = True

if age >= 18:
    if has_license:
        print("You can drive")
    else:
        print("You need a license to drive")
else:
    print("You are too young to drive")`}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">Conditional Expressions & Operators</h2>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-lg p-3 sm:p-4 my-4">
      <pre class="text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap"><code>{`# Multiple conditions with logical operators
age = 25
income = 50000

if age >= 18 and income > 30000:
    print("You qualify for the loan")

# Using 'or' operator
day = "Saturday"
if day == "Saturday" or day == "Sunday":
    print("It's the weekend!")

# Using 'not' operator
is_raining = False
if not is_raining:
    print("You don't need an umbrella")

# Ternary operator (conditional expression)
age = 20
status = "adult" if age >= 18 else "minor"
print(status)  # adult

# Chained comparisons
x = 15
if 10 <= x <= 20:
    print("x is between 10 and 20")

# Checking multiple values
fruit = "apple"
if fruit in ["apple", "banana", "orange"]:
    print("This is a common fruit")

# Truthy and Falsy values
name = ""
if name:  # False if empty string
    print(f"Hello, {name}")
else:
    print("Please enter your name")

number = 0
if number:  # False if 0
    print("Number is non-zero")
else:
    print("Number is zero")`}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6 mt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mb-3">Python Truthy & Falsy Values</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-4">
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">Falsy</strong>: <code class="bg-custom-primary text-custom-secondary px-1 rounded text-sm">False, None, 0, 0.0, "", [], (), {}, set()</code></li>
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">Truthy</strong>: Everything else</li>
        <li>Use proper indentation (4 spaces) for code blocks</li>
        <li>Avoid deep nesting - consider using functions</li>
        <li>Use descriptive condition names for complex logic</li>
        <li>Leverage <code class="bg-custom-primary text-custom-secondary px-1 rounded text-sm">in</code> operator for membership testing</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</SidebarLayout>